WEBVTT

00:00:00.530 --> 00:00:05.770
In the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, amen.

00:00:05.770 --> 00:00:12.170
The reading from the Sinaxadion from A4, on which we commemorate the holy martyr Belagia

00:00:12.170 --> 00:00:14.410
of Tarsus.

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:19.450
Saint Belagia came from a noble family of Tarsus, Celicia.

00:00:19.450 --> 00:00:25.690
She settled in Rome and became betrothed to one of the sons of the Emperor Diocletian.

00:00:25.690 --> 00:00:31.770
Having heard of the rapid spread of the Christian faith, she sought to learn what it taught.

00:00:31.770 --> 00:00:37.410
A short time later, in a dream, she saw the Bishop of Rome baptizing a great number

00:00:37.410 --> 00:00:39.570
of Catecumans.

00:00:39.570 --> 00:00:45.610
He turned towards her and called her to be reborn to eternal life.

00:00:45.610 --> 00:00:51.250
When she awoke, Belagia took leave of her parents, under the pretext of going to visit

00:00:51.250 --> 00:00:56.370
her nurse, and went with haste to the Bishop who baptized her.

00:00:56.370 --> 00:01:01.690
She gave her rich garments to the prelate, so that he might distribute them to the poor,

00:01:01.690 --> 00:01:08.450
and arrived at the house of her nurse, very simply dressed in the style of the common people.

00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:12.530
As her nurse would not receive her, she went home.

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:18.570
Her mother, seeing her clothes, realized what had happened and tried to persuade her daughter

00:01:18.570 --> 00:01:25.090
to forsake Christ and to dress herself in a manner appropriate to her status.

00:01:25.090 --> 00:01:30.050
The young girl, however, remained unyielding and proclaimed that she would never abandon

00:01:30.050 --> 00:01:32.610
the spouse of her soul.

00:01:32.610 --> 00:01:38.770
Her mother informed Diocletian's son that her daughter refused his offer of marriage,

00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:43.410
and he, in desperation, committed suicide.

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:48.570
When the emperor heard this news, he was filled with a violent rage and had the saint

00:01:48.570 --> 00:01:57.570
shut up in a red-hot bronze ox, in which she accomplished her definitive union with Christ.

00:01:57.570 --> 00:02:03.530
Through the prayers of our holy fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us

00:02:03.530 --> 00:02:04.370
and save us.
